#### Issue details

Description for [ShapeRenderer#line(float x, float y, float z, float x2, float y2, float z2, Color c1, Color c2)](https://libgdx.badlogicgames.com/nightlies/docs/api/com/badlogic/gdx/graphics/glutils/ShapeRenderer.html#line-float-float-float-float-float-float-com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Color-com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Color-) says _"Draws a line using ShapeRenderer.ShapeType.Line or ShapeRenderer.ShapeType.Filled. The line is drawn with two colors interpolated between the start and end points."_, but in fact color args are ignored with ShapeType.Filled:

``` java
public void line (float x, float y, float z, float x2, float y2, float z2, Color c1, Color c2) {
    if (shapeType == ShapeType.Filled) {
        rectLine(x, y, x2, y2, defaultRectLineWidth);
        return;
    }
    // ...
}
```

Maybe this method should throw an exception if used with ShapeType.Filled saying "use rectLine instead" or have a different description in docs (this method works, but not as expected)
#### Reproduction steps/code

``` java
ShapeRenderer shapeRenderer = new ShapeRenderer();
shapeRenderer.begin(ShapeRenderer.ShapeType.Filled);
shapeRenderer.line(5f, 5f, 10f, 10f, Color.RED, Color.GREEN);
shapeRenderer.end();
```
#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies

1.9.3

Libgdx exposes it's built-in logger through `Gdx.app.log` methods. From what I can gather, these log messages are always sent to stdout as that is the default behavior of the lwjgl logger. 

I suggest adding a feature which would allow developers to change that default behavior and set a different output stream/writer, add new writers, or hook onto the current log methods so that they might also be output somewhere else (such as a file or dev console).

For example, let's say that the game has a dev console and we wish to redirect all logging calls to the in-game dev console instead of stdout. Ideally it would look something like this:

```
// Create a custom output writer
public class ConsoleWriter extends Writer     
     //........
     public void write(char cbuf[], int off, int len) throws IOException {
           console.write(cbuf, off, len);
     }
     //........
}

Gdx.app.setLogWriter(new ConsoleWriter()); 
// from this point on all Gdx.app.log/error/debug invocations will write to the ConsoleWriter instead of stdout
```
